This paper is about reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper proposes a new algorithm for policy optimization, which is a common problem in reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the application of the algorithm on Atari game playing tasks and benchmark control tasks, which suggests that it may fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of convolutional neural networks, which is a common technique in computer vision, indicating that it may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the theoretical target for adaptive policy improvement, which suggests that it may also fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
